OL,3,CError sees private patients given
OL,4,Cexpensive prescriptions for free
OL,6,FIt was seen as "a signficiant
OL,7,Fmilestone" to streamline the process,
OL,8,Fimproving efficiency and reducing the
OL,9,Flikelihood of prescribing errors.
OL,11,FDeputy Binet explains: "When we
OL,12,Fimplemented the new automatic
OL,13,Fprescriptions it became apparent that
OL,14,Fsome private prescriptions were
OL,15,Factually being issued on the State.
OL,17,F"What has transpired is that there are
OL,18,Flaws in place that require private
OL,19,Fprescriptions to be paid for and
OL,20,Fpublic prescriptions not.
