OL,3,CError sees private patients given
OL,4,Cexpensive prescriptions for free
OL,6,F"It is recognised that some patients
OL,7,Fmay find that they cannot pay for high-
OL,8,Fcost drugs privately. Any patient in
OL,9,Fthis position will be given the option
OL,10,Fto return to the public sector and
OL,11,Freceive treatment in line with HCS
OL,12,Fprotocols and NICE guidance.
OL,14,F"Those patients who decide to remain
OL,15,Fprivate patients will be charged. All
OL,16,Fother private prescriptions, and those
OL,17,Ftaken to the community pharmacy, will
OL,18,Fbe charged for accordingly."
